The article is a transcript of a press conference with President Biden and Prime Minister Draghi at the Chigi Palace in Rome, Italy. The president confirms that the Pope blessed his rosary and that they discussed climate and the "Build Back Better" initiative. When asked about the issue of abortion, the president says it did not come up and that they talked about him being a good Catholic and receiving Communion. However, he did not receive Communion from the Pope during their meeting. The president declines to discuss the U.S. Conference of Bishops, stating that it was a private conversation.